 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align dashboard and alternate renderers with snapshot and attention sections","description":"Align the TUI dashboard and alternate renderer flows with the same snapshot and attention section model. This task exists because the dashboard should share the robot mental model rather than presenting a separate worldview that only coincidentally overlaps.","design":"The work should decide how dashboard screens, terse output, markdown output, and TOON output consume shared sections, summary metadata, and diagnostics or explainability affordances. It should explicitly preserve legitimate UI-specific affordances while preventing them from becoming a separate semantic branch, so human operators can answer why questions without diverging from machine-consumable semantics.\n\nThe result should be that snapshot and attention are conceptually recognizable everywhere.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when dashboard and alternate renderer experiences clearly reuse the shared section model and no longer depend on divergent state assembly paths.","notes":"Parity here improves operator ergonomics for both human and machine users, because it makes the product's mental model consistent.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:12:25.509728143Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dashboard","parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.434476151Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.967287453Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"20